"false\" Priority=\"72\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\r\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Colorful List Accent 6\"></w:LsdException>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"73\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\r\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Colorful Grid Accent 6\"></w:LsdException>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"19\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\r\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Subtle Emphasis\"></w:LsdException>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"21\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\r\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Intense Emphasis\"></w:LsdException>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"31\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\r\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Subtle Reference\"></w:LsdException>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"32\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\r\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Intense Reference\"></w:LsdException>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"33\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\r\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Book Title\"></w:LsdException>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"37\" Name=\"Bibliography\"></w:LsdException>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"39\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"TOC Heading\"></w:LsdException>\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-priority:99;\r\n	mso-style-qformat:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin-top:0in;\r\n	mso-para-margin-right:0in;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:10.0pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin-left:0in;\r\n	line-height:115%;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:11.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Calibri\",\"sans-serif\";\r\n	mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\r\n	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;\r\n	mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\r\n	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\n	mso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\n	mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><b>DAY 01: ARRIVAL IN MEDAN (Emerald Garden Hotel / Le Polonia Hotel / or similar)<br></b>Upon arrival at Kualanamu International Airport pick up by our tour guide and then Transfer to hotel, afternoon free at own leisure.<br><b><br>DAY 02: MEDAN â€“ CITY TOUR â€“ TANGKAHAN&nbsp; (Mega Inn Lodge)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast city tour visiting Sultan Palace, Great Mosque, Chinese Temple and then drive to Tangkahan via Binjai and Batang Serangan. Afternoon arrival at Tangkahan check in MEGA INN<br><b><br>DAY 03: TANGKAHAN â€“ ELEPHANT WASHING &amp; RIVER SAFARI&nbsp;&nbsp; (B,L)<br></b>After breakfast walking to the elephant station and then join&nbsp; with the Mahout during washing the Elephants, and feed the elephants, after feeding the Elephant enjoying Tubing through the river and stop will be made at fantastic Buluh Waterfall where you may enjoy the waterfall, take natural shower and enjoy sun-bathing and swimming on the river. Enjoy picnic lunch on the bank of the river. Afternoon arrival at the village you can get in touch with local people, where you can see the daily activities of the local people and then return to guest house by walking, arrival at guest house you can take a rest or visit hotsprings and waterfall near the guest house.<br><b><br>DAY 04: TANGKAHAN â€“ BUKIT LAWANG BY JEEP (Bukit Lawang Cottage / The Heritage Hotel / Rindu Alam Hotel)&nbsp;&nbsp; (B) <br></b>After breakfast leave Tangkahan for Bukit Lawang by Jeep passing plantation and jungle road, on the way stop at plantation and several interesting places for enjoying the panorama and witness the activities of the local people. Upon arrival at Bukit Lawang check in to hotel.<br><b><br>DAY 05: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ TRACKING&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast walking to the jungle to start a jungle tracking to explore the nature of Leuser National Park with their flora and fauna, there will be possibility to see Orang Utan in their own habitat and other kind of animals such as Thomas leaf monkeys, long tail maccaque, gibbon, black gibbon and other kind of flora and fauna of tropical rain forest. This tracking will take about 03 hours, after tracking return to hotel.<br>Afternoon free at own leisure to enjoy the nature of Bukit Lawang where you can also walking to the village around the hotel.<br><b><br>DAY 06: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ BRASTAGI (Sinabung Hills Hotel / Sibayak Intl Hotel / Grand Mutiara Hotel)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Brastagi, on the way stop at Sembahe River, passing Sibolangit, and arrival at Brastagi visiting Lhumbini Park with its duplicate of Shwedagon pagoda, then visit fruit market and Gundaling Hill. Afternoon check in to hotel.<br><b><br>DAY 07: BRASTAGI â€“ SAMOSIR / LAKE TOBA&nbsp;&nbsp; (Tabo Cottages / Toledo Inn / Samosir Villas)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Samosir, on the way visit Batak Karo traditional village at Dokan, stop at Sipiso-piso waterfall, visiting â€œRumah Bolonâ€ (Long House) the old Palace of Batak Simalungun Kings and stop at Simarjarunjung to enjoy the fantastic view of Lake Toba. Arrival at Parapat crossing to Samosir Island by ferry boat, arriving on Samosir Island check in to hotel.<br><b><br>DAY 08: SAMOSIR â€“ EXCURISON BY CAR&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast excursion on Samosir Island by car, visiting several Batak Toba traditional villages at :<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ambarita : To see stone chairs and tables the old meeting place of Sialagan Kings.<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Simanindo : To see Batak Toba traditional dances and museum.<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pangururan : To see the view of Lake Toba and Hot springs water.<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tomok : To see the old tombs of Sidabutar Kings<br>along on this trip also possible to stop at school to see the activities of young children in the school, visiting the village where the people make traditional hand weaving + stop also at scenic places like the graves! Afternoon return back to hotel.<br><b><br>DAY 09: SAMOSIR â€“ SIPIROK&nbsp; (Tor Sibohi Hotel)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast crossing back to Parapat and arrival at Parapat drive to Sipirok, on the way stop at pineapple, clove and coffee plantation and visiting traditional market at Balige Sigur-gur and Sipoholon hotsprings. Before arrival at Sipirok, enjoy the nature by walking at the bank of Sarulla river, the ricefield-terraces and arrival at Sipirok check in to hotel.<br><b><br>DAY 10: SIPIROK â€“ BUKITTINGGI (Royal Denai Hotel / Simila)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>Leave Sipirok for Bukittinggi by passing rain tropical forest of Rimba Panti and stop will be made to see the attraction of monkey picking up the coconut. Visit pepper, vanilla, cardamom and cinnamon garden, and crossing the equator line at Bonjol, afternoon arrival at Bukittinggi - the charming town of Minangkabau people - directly check in to hotel.<br><b><br>DAY 11: BUKITTINGGI â€“ MINANGKABAU TOUR&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Batusangkar via Tabek Patah, on the way stop at Rao-Rao to visit Minangkabau traditional village and stop to see traditional coffee milling, arrival at Batusangkar drive to Pagaruyung to visit the duplicate of the Palace of Minangkabau Kingdom, afternoon return to Bukittinggi via Padang Panjang and visit Pandai Sikat village to see Minangkabau traditional hand weaving and wood carving, arrival at Bukittinggi city tour visiting Sianok Canyon (from the panorama point), Fort-De-Kock, Museum and Market. Afternoon return to hotel.<br><b><br>DAY 12: VILLAGE TOUR BY BICYCLE&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Panampuang village, it will take about 30 minutes driving from your hotel in Bukittinggi, arrival at Panampuang village visiting traditional embroidery and then start the trip with bicycle to explore the villages where you will stop at rice field to see the farmer working on rice field traditionally during planting the rice or harvest time, you may also try and join with the farmer during working at rice field, then continue by bicycle to visit school in the village and keep in touch with local peoples in the village during their daily activities such as making traditional handy craft or snack,&nbsp; you can also stop at coffee shop in the village to try traditional coffee and get in touch with the villagers at coffee shop, since coffee shop is used by the villagers for social contact. Afternoon return to hotel in Bukittinggi.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><b>DAY 13: BUKITTINGGI â€“ PADANG / AIRPORT&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After brekfast drive to Padang via Anai Valley, on the way stop at Anai Waterfall, arrival at Padang directly transfer to Airport.<br><b><br>INCLUDED :<br></b>- Accommodation based on twin sharing room at above mentioned hotels<br>- private air-conditioned car / tourist coach<br>- Daily breakfast<br>- Tours<br>- Transfer<br>- Entrance fee<br>- Elephant washing at Tangkahan + elephant feeding<br>- Tubing at Tangkahan + picnic lunch<br>- Jeep (Tangkahan â€“ Bukit Lawang)<br>- Tracking at Bukit Lawang (03 hours) included local guide and permit <br>- Return ferry boat for crossing from Parapat to Samosir Island<br>- Bicycle trip at Bukittinggi<br>- English speaking tour guide.<br><b><br>EXCLUDED :<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </b>Airfares, airport taxes, insurance, donation, tips, elephant riding at Tangkahan, camera permit at Bukit Lawang and all personal gratuities.</p>'),
(13, '09 DAYS /08 Nights  NORTH  SUMATRA SPECIAL - NATURE AND TROPICAL ADVENTURE ', 'Take a tour through Medan, seeing Maimoon Palace, the Great Mosque and a Chinese temple- evidence of Medanâ€™s cultural diversity.<br><br>Spend a morning with Sumatran elephants, bathing the gentle giants and Tubing at Buluh River.<br><br>Trek through Gunung Leuser National Park to spot Sumatran orangutans in their natural habitat, an incredible wildlife experience.<br><br>Get the blood pumping with an active adventure around North Sumatra. Venture into the wilds to meet elephants, monkeys and orangutans and take a spectacular drive through highland landscapes. Continue to Lake Toba, the worldâ€™s largest volcanic lake, to explore ethnic villages with distinctive cultures. <br><br><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:=\"\" in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"></span>\r\n\r\n					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                ', '', '<p><b>DAY 01: ARRIVAL IN MEDAN (Le Polonia Hotel / Emerald Garden Hotel / similar)<br></b>Upon arrival at KUALANAMU INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT pick up by our tour guide and then transfer to hotel, afternoon free at own leisure.<br><br><b>DAY 02: MEDAN â€“ CITY TOUR â€“ TANGKAHAN (Mega Inn Lodge)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast, pick up by our tour guide and then transfer to town for city tour visiting Sultan Palace, Great Mosque, Chinese Temple and then drive to Tangkahan via Binjai and Batang Serangan. Afternoon arrival at Tangkahan check in Mega Inn Lodge.<br><br><b>DAY 03: TANGKAHAN â€“ ELEPHANT WASHING &amp; RIVER SAFARI&nbsp;&nbsp; (B,L)<br></b>After breakfast walking to the elephants station and then join with the Mahout during washing the elephants, and then feed the elephant. After feeding the elephant enjoying Tubing through the river and stop will be made at fantastic Buluh Waterfall where you may enjoy the waterfall, take natural shower, enjoy sun-bathing and swimming on the river and enjoying picnic lunch on the bank of the river. In afternoon arrival at the village you can get in touch with local people, where you can see the daily activities of the local people and then return to guesthouse by walking, arrival at guest house you can take a rest or visit hot springs and waterfall near the guest house.<br><br><b>DAY 04: TANGKAHAN â€“ BUKIT LAWANG BY JEEP (Bukit Lawang Cottages / The Heritage Hotel / Rindu Alam Hotel)&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast leave Tangkahan for Bukit Lawang by Jeep passing plantation and jungle road, on the way stop at plantation and several interesting places such as school, palm oil factory (from its outside only) and for enjoying the panorama and witness the activities of the local people. Upon arrival at Bukit Lawang check-in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 05: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ TRACKING&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast walking to the jungle to start a jungle tracking to explore the nature of Leuser National park with their flora and fauna, there is possibility to see Orang Utan on their own habitat and other kind of animal such as Thomas leaf monkeys, long tail macaque, gibbon, black gibbon and other kind of flora and fauna of tropical rain forest. This tracking will take about 03 hours, after tracking return to hotel. Afternoon free at own leisure to enjoy the nature of Bukit Lawang where you can also walking to the village around the hotel<br><br><b>DAY 06: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ BRASTAGI (Sinabung Hills / Sibayak Intl Hotel / Grand Mutiara Hotel)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Brastagi , on the way stop at Sembahe River, passing Sibolangit, and arrival at Brastagi visiting Lhumbini Park with its duplicate of Shwedagon pagoda, then visit fruit market, and Gundaling Hill. Afternoon check in to hotel.<br>&nbsp;<br><b>DAY 07: BRASTAGI â€“ SAMOSIR / LAKE TOBA (Tabo Cottages / Toledo Inn)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Samosir , on the way visit Batak Karo traditional village at â€œDokanâ€, stop at Sipiso-piso waterfall, visiting â€œRumah Bolonâ€ (Long House) the old Palace of Batak Simalungun Kings and stop at Simarjarunjung to enjoy the fantastic view of Lake Toba. Arrival at Parapat crossing to Samosir Island by ferry boat, arrival at Samosir Island check-in to hotel.<br>&nbsp;<br><b>DAY 08: SAMOSIR â€“ EXCURISON BY CAR&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast excursion on Samosir Island by car, visiting several Batak Toba traditional villages at :<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ambarita : To see stone chairs and tables the old meeting place of Sialagan Kings.<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Simanindo : To see Batak Toba traditional dances and museum.<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pangururan : To see the view of Lake Toba and Hot springs water.<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tomok : To see the old tomb of Sidabutar Kings<br>along on this trip also possible to stop at school to see the activities of young children in the school, visiting the village where the people make traditional hand weaving + stop also at scenic places like the graves! Afternoon return back to hotel<br><br><b>DAY 09: SAMOSIR â€“ MEDAN / AIRPORT&nbsp;&nbsp; (B)<br></b>After breakfast crossing by public ferry to Paarapat and then drive back to Medan via Pematang Siantar and Tebing Tinggi, on the way stop at several plantation, and it will take about 5 hours driving. Arrival in Medan directly transfer to airport to catch the flight to next destination. TOUR ENDS<br></p><p><b>Included :<br></b>- Accommodation based on twin sharing room at above mentioned hotels <br>- private air-conditioned car / tourist coach <br>- Daily breakfast <br>- Tours <br>- Transfer <br>- Entrance fee <br>- Elephant washing at Tangkahan + elephant feeding <br>- Tubing at Tangkahan + picnic lunch <br>- Jeep (Tangkahan â€“ Bukit Lawang) <br>- Tracking at Bukit Lawang (03 hours) included local guide and permit<br>- Ferry boat crossing from Parapat to Samosir V.V, English speaking tour guide.<br><br><b>EXCLUDED :<br></b>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Airfares, airport taxes, insurance, donation, tips, elephant riding at Tangkahan, camera permit at Bukit Lawang and all personal gratuities.<br></p>'),
(15, '05 DAYS / 04 NIGHTS EXPLORE SIBERUT â€“ MENTAWAI PRIMITIVE TRIBE', '<div align=\"justify\">Mentawai tribe living deep in the forests of Siberut Island who were still practising the ancient traditions and rituals of their indigenous culture.<br>Learn about the Mentawai Tribe and join in everydayâ€™s activities! From hunting to fishing, youâ€™ll&nbsp; learn every little secret about the Mentawai people. Explore and enjoy the natural surroundings, jump in the river for a refresh, try local food and stay at a homestay with the locals. It will be an unforgettable adventure in Sumatra <br></div>					                                					                                ', '', '<div align=\"justify\"><b>DAY 01 (Tuesday) : PADANG â€“ SIBERUT â€“ BAT OBAY / BAT ROROGOT&nbsp;&nbsp; (L,D)<br></b>After early breakfast, driver will pick you up at the hotel and then transfer to harbor to catch fast boat to Muara Siberut, fast boat leaving at 07.00AM, this ferry will stop at Sikabaluan and continue to Siberut, arrive in Siberut around 13.00PM and meet with our guide, prepare and report to authority for trekking, continue by local canoe motor in the River, stay in Bat Obay / Bat Rorogot.<br>&nbsp;<br><b>DAY 02 (Wednesday) : EXPLORING THE NATIVEâ€™S ACTIVITIES IN BAT OBAI / ROROGOT â€“ BUTUI&nbsp;&nbsp; (B,L,D)<br></b>Wake up for a bath in the river. After having breakfast exploring the daily activities of Nativeâ€™s Mentawai tribe such as : making loincloth, fishing and making tattoo and then continue your trip to Butui by local motorize canoe, it will take about 3-4 hours, arrival at Butui village stay at traditional house of Mentawai called â€œUMAâ€.<br><br><b>DAY 03 (Thursday) : EXPLORING THE NATIVEâ€™S ACTIVITIES IN BUTUI&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (B,L,D)<br></b>After breakfast in the morning, prepare to explore the Nativeâ€™s Mentawai activities, you will see how the mentawai making poisoneous arrow for hunting and then go for hunting in the jungle&nbsp; with Mentawai after hunting you will see how they make Sago (main food of Mentawai people) and search for Sago worm and then you will see how to make traditional medicine. Evening you can enjoy traditional dance of Mentawai and also possible to arrange pig feast (traditional dance and pig feast are optional).<br>&nbsp;<br><b>DAY 04 (Friday) : BUTUI â€“ MUNTEI (B,L,D)<br></b>After breakfast, you still have time to enjoy and see the activities of Mentawai people and then leaving to Muntei Village by traditional motorized canoe , on the way stop at Kulukubuk to visit waterfall in the forest, you can swim at waterfall and then return to river to continue your trip to Muntei village, arrival at Muntei village transfer to traditional house of Mentawai or to guesthouse for overnight.<br>&nbsp;<br><b>DAY 05 (Saturday) : MUNTEI â€“ MUARA SIBERUT â€“ PADANG (B,L)<br></b>After breakfast free at own leisure or explore the village, at noon transfer to Muara Siberut to catch fast ferry to Padang, arrive at early evening in Padang. Transfer to your hotel.<br><b><br>INCLUDED:</b><br>- Meals as specified in the Itinerary, All food brought from Padang,&nbsp;&nbsp; along the Journey in the island the food is carried by porters and cooked by Guide and helped by his crew.<br>- Return transfer frm hotel or Airport to harbor by Car<br>- Transfer Padang â€“ Siberut by Regular Fast Ferry vice-versa <br>- Transfer Siberut â€“ Village through river by motorize canoe vv<br>- Accommodation in the jungle at the local house (UMA)<br>- Licensed English &amp; Mentawai Speaking Guide <br>- Meals during the trip prepared by guide and cook<br>- Stay in UMA (Mentawai traditional house) with thin matrass and Mosquito Net<br>- Guide and Cook<br>&nbsp;<br><b>EXCLUDED: <br></b>- Personal Expenses<br>- The Expenses of Out of the Programme <br>- Accommodation &amp; Meals in Padang<br>- Personal Insurance<br>- Any additional costs which might appear caused by delay or cancel of the Fast boat.<br></div>                                                                                                        ');
INSERT INTO `paket_wisata` (`id`, `nama`, `deskripsi`, `peta`, `timeline`) VALUES
(19, '13 DAYS / 12 NIGHTS WONDERS NATURE OF NORTH SUMATRA AND FANTASTIC BEACH OF WEH ISLAND', '-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Observing critically endangered Sumatran orangutans in their natural habitat, Sumatra Elephant and enjoy the beauty of Lake Toba<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exploring nature and villages, see sumatra elephants, orangutans and relax at Lake Toba<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Hidden Paradise of Tangkahan, Sumatra Elephant, Orang Utan and The beauty of Lake Toba<br>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Explore the beauty of Weh Island with its white sandy beach and great place for snorkeling &amp; diving<br>					                                ', '', '<div><b>DAY 01: ARRIVAL IN MEDAN (Emerald Garden Hotel / Le Polonia Hotel /or similar hotel)Â </b></div><div>Upon arrival at KUALANAMU INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT pick up by our tour guide and then Transfer to hotel, afternoon free at own leisure.</div><div><br></div><div><b>DAY 02: MEDANâ€“ CITY TOUR â€“ TANGKAHAN (MEGA INN)Â  Â  (B)</b></div><div>After breakfast, pick up by our tour guide and then transfer to town for city tour visiting Sultan Palace, Great Mosque, Chinese Temple and then drive to Tangkahan via Binjai and BatangSerangan. Afternoon arrival at Tangkahan check in MEGA INN</div><div><br></div><div><b>DAY 03. TANGKAHAN â€“ ELEPHANT WASHING & RIVER SAFARIÂ  Â (B/ L)</b></div><div>After breakfast walking to the elpahant station and then joinÂ  with the Mahout during washing the Elephant, and then feed the elephant, after feeding the Elephant enjoying tubing through the river and stop will be made at Fantastic Buluh Waterfall where you may enjoy the waterfall where you can take nature shower and then you can enjoy sun bathing and swimming on the river and enjoying picnic lunch on the beach of the river. Afternoon arrival at the village you can get in touch with local people, where you can see the daily activities of the local people and then return to guest house by walking, arrival at guest house you can take a rest or visit hot springs and waterfall near the guest house.Â </div><div><br></div><div><b>DAY 04. TANGKAHAN â€“ BUKIT LAWANG BY Jeep (Ecolodge Bukit Lawang Cottages /RinduAlam Hotel / Wisma Leuser Sibayak)Â  (B)</b></div><div>After breakfast leave Tangkahan for Bukit Lawang by Jeep passing plantation and jungle road, on the way stop at plantation and several interesting places such as school, palm oil factory (from its outside only) and for enjoying the panorama and witness the activities of the local people. Upon arrival at Bukit Lawang check-in to hotel.Â </div><div><br></div><div><b>DAY 05. BUKIT LAWANG â€“ TRACKINGÂ  Â (B)</b></div><div>After breakfast walking to the jungle to start a jungle tracking to explore the nature of Leuser National park with their flora and fauna, the possibility to see Orang Utan on their own habitat and other kind of animal such as Thomas leaf monkeys, long tail macaque, gibbon, black gibbon and other kind of flora and fauna of tropical rain forest. This tracking will take about 03 hours, after tracking return to hotel.</div><div>Afternoon free at own leisure to enjoy the nature of Bukit Lawang where you can also walkingto the village around the hotel</div><div><br></div><div><b>DAY 06. BUKIT LAWANG â€“ BRASTAGI (Sinabung Hills/Sibayak Int Htl/Grand Mutiara Hotel) BÂ Â </b></div><div>After breakfast drive to Brastagi, on the way stop at Sembahe River, passing Sibolangit, and arrival at Brastagi visiting LhumbiniPark with its duplicate of Shwedagon pagoda, then visit fruit market, and Gundaling Hill. Afternoon check in to hotel.</div><div><br></div><div><b>DAY 07. BRASTAGI â€“ SAMOSIRÂ  (Tabo Cottages / Toledo Inn)Â  (B)</b></div><div>At 07.30 AM after breakfast drive to Parapat, on the way visit BatakKaro traditional village at Dokan, Sipiso-piso waterfall, RumahBolon (Long House) the old palace of BatakSimalungun Kings and Simarjarunjung to see the view of Lake Toba, upon arrival at Parapat crossing to Samosir Island by ferry boat , arrival at Samosir check in to hotel.</div><div><br></div><div><b>DAY 08. SAMOSIR EXCURSION BY CAR (B)</b></div><div>At 07.30 AM after breakfast excursion on Samosir Island by car, visiting several Batak Toba traditional villages at :</div><div>â€¢<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Ambarita : To see stone chairs and tables the old meeting place of Sialagan Kings.</div><div>â€¢<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Simanindo : To see Batak Toba traditional dances and museum.</div><div>â€¢<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Pangururan : To see the view of Lake Toba and Hot springs water.</div><div>â€¢<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Tomok : To see the old tombs of Sidabutar Kings</div><div>Along on this trip also possible to stop at school to see the activities of young children in the school, visiting the village where the people make traditional hand weaving + stop also at scenic places like the graves! Afternoon return back to hotel</div><div><br></div><div><b>DAY 09. SAMOSIR â€“ MEDAN (Prime Plaza Kuala Namu / Horison Sky Kuala Namu Hotel) B</b></div><div>After breakfast crossing back to Parapat and then drive Medan via PematangSiantar and Tebing Tinggi, stop will be made at several interesting places. and afternoon city tour visiting Sultan Palace, Great Mosque, Chinese Temple and Kesawan Area ( Formerly the center of Medan City during Dutch time)</div><div><br></div><div><b>DAY 10. MEDANâ€“AIRPORT â€“ BANDA ACEH - PULAU WEH (Freddieâ€™s SantaiSumurTiga / Casa Nemo Resort) B</b></div><div>At 06:00AM after early breakfast, please check-out from hotel and walk up to the third floor of the hotel to reach your check-in airport counter for your flight Kualanamu Medan - Banda Aceh by Citilink QG-10 leaving at 07:50AM, at 08:55AM arrival at Banda Aceh Airport pick-up by our driver and then short city tour in Banda Aceh accompanied by the driver visiting Grand Mosque, Tsunami Museum, Banda Aceh traditional house and Kapal Apung â€œ A big Electric vessel was moved from the ocean during Trunami disaster.</div><div><br></div><div>At 14:30PM transferred to the Banda Aceh harbour for taking the ferry leaving at 16:00PM</div><div>Arriving at Balohan port in Sabang/Pulau Weh pick-up by our another driver and then transferred to hotel.</div><div><br></div><div><b>DAY 11.Â  WEH ISLAND â€“ OWN PROGRAM (B)</b></div><div>During your stay in PulauWeh there are plenty of options to do; snorkeling, scuba diving, fishing trips, sunset cruises, sightseeing inside the peaceful island and many others. All can be arranged with your hotel and the cost at personal account (Transport and tour guide not provided)</div><div><br></div><div><b>DAY 12. WEH ISLAND â€“ OWN PROGRAM (B)</b></div><div>During your stay in PulauWeh there are plenty of options to do; snorkeling, scuba diving, fishing trips, sunset cruises, sightseeing inside the peaceful island and many others. All can be arranged with your hotel and the cost at personal account (Transport and tour guide not provided)</div><div><br></div><div><b>DAY 13. PULAU WEH â€“ AIRPORT(B)</b></div><div>After breakfast transfer toÂ  harbour to catch ferry for Banda Aceh, arrival at Banda Aceh harbour pick up by driver and then transfer to airport for your flight to next destination.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Included:<br></b>-Â Â Â  Accommodation based on twin / triple sharing room<br>-Â Â Â  Air condition private car (Except during stay at Weh Island)<br>-Â Â Â  Daily breakfast<br>-Â Â Â  Tours<br>-Â Â Â  Transfers<br>-Â Â Â  Entrance fee<br>-Â Â Â  English speaking tour guide from Day 01 untilDday 09<br>-Â Â Â  Elephant washing + elephant feeding at Tangkahan<br>-Â Â Â  Tubing at Tangkahan + picnic lunch<br>-Â Â Â  Local jeep for transfer from Tangkahan to Bukit Lawang<br>-Â Â Â  Jungle tracking at Bukit Lawang (03 hours) included: local guide and permit<br>-Â Â Â  One way flight ticket Medan â€“ Sabang (Weh Island) by Garuda Indonesia on economy class<br>-Â Â Â  One way fast boat for crossing from Weh Island to Banda Aceh<br>-Â Â Â  Transfer from Sabang Airport to hotel in Weh Island<br>-Â Â Â  Transfer from hotel in Weh Island to harbor<br>-Â Â Â  Transfer from Banda Aceh harbor to Banda Aceh airport</div><div><br></div><div><b>Excluded:<br></b>-Â Â Â  Other airfares, airport taxes, insurance, donations, tips, lunch, dinner, elephant riding at Tangkahan, camera permit at National Park and all personal gratuities.<br><br></div><div><br></div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        '),
(20, '15 DAYS  MEDAN â€“ BUKIT LAWANG â€“ LAKE TOBA â€“ BARUMUN NWS -  KERINCI SEBLAT â€“ PADANG OVERLAND TOURS- A', 'Incredible trip to see Sumatra Orang Utan and The Biggest Volcanic Lake In South East Asia.<br>Great Experiences, adventure, nature, culture and leisure.<br>Discover the highligh of Sumatra tour<br>Giving The Animals Peace And Dignity<br><br>Explore Barumun Nagari Sanctuary, preserve the wild animals that are not neglected. All heans in Barumun Nagari are kept alive in the wild, within the guarded and supervised area.<br>Tracking, enjoying the nature of Kerinci Seblat National park and explore Kubu tribe<br>Exotic tropical rain forest of Kerinci Seblat and Nomadic Kubu tribe<br>Wild life, animal, tropical rain forest<br>', '', '                                                                                                                                                            <div align=\"justify\"><b>DAY 01: AIRPORT / MEDAN â€“ HOTEL (Emerald Garden Hotel / Le Polonia Hotel /Similar) </b><br>Upon arrival at Kualanamu International Airport transfer to hotel and afternoon free at own leisure.<br><br><b>DAY 02: MEDAN â€“ BUKIT LAWANG (Bukit Lawang Cottages / Rindu Alam Hotel) (B)</b><br>After\r\n breakfast city tour by visiting great Mosque, Sultan Palace and Chinese\r\n temple, then drive to Bukit Lawang, on the way stop at Palm oil and \r\nrubber plantation, upon arrival at Bukit Lawang check in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 03: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ JUNGLE TRACKING / VISIT ORANGÂ  UTANÂ Â  (B)</b><br>After\r\n breakfast walking to the jungle to start a jungle tracking to explore \r\nthe nature of Leuser National park with their flora and fauna, the \r\npossibility to see Orang Utan on their own habitat and other kind of \r\nanimal such as Thomas leaf monkeys, long tail macaque, gibbon, black \r\ngibbon and other kind of flora and fauna of tropical rain forest. This \r\ntracking will take about 03 hours, after tracking return to hotel.<br>Afternoon free at own leisure to enjoy the nature of Bukit Lawang where you can also walkingÂ  to the village around the hotel. <br><br><b>DAY 04: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ BRASTAGI (Sinabung Hills/Sibayak Int Htl/Grand Mutiara Htl) (B)</b><br>After\r\n breakfast drive to Brastagi via Sembahe and Sibolangit, arrival in \r\nBrastagi visiting Lumbhini park with its duplicate of Shwedagon temple \r\nand then visit fruit market, afternoon check in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 05: BRASTAGI â€“ SAMOSIR (Tabo Cottages / Samosir Villa/ Toledo Inn )Â Â  (B)</b><br>After\r\n breakfast drive to Parapat on the way visit Batak Karo traditional \r\nvillage at Dokan, Sipiso-piso waterfall, Rumah Bolan ( Long House ) the \r\nold palace of Batak Simalungun Kings and Simarjarunjung to see the view \r\nof Lake Toba, upon arrival at Parapat crossing to Samosir Island by \r\nferry boat arrival at Samosir check in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 06: SAMOSIR EXCURSIONÂ Â  (B)</b><br>After breakfast excursion on Samosir Island by car, visiting several Batak Toba traditional villages:<br>-Â Â  Â Ambarita : To see stone chairs and table the old meeting place of Sialagan Kings.<br>-Â Â  Â Simanindo : To see Batak Toba traditional dance and museum.<br>-Â Â  Â Pangururan : To see the view of Lake Toba and Hot springs water.<br>-Â Â  Â Tomok : To see the old tomb of Sidabutar Kings<br>along\r\n On this trip also possible to stop at school to see the activities of \r\nyoung children in the school, visiting the village where the people make\r\n traditional hand weaving.+ stop also at scenic places like the graves! \r\nAfternoon return back to hotel<br><br><b>DAY 07: SAMOSIR â€“ SIPIROK (Tor Sibohi Hotel)Â Â Â  (B)</b><br>After\r\n breakfast crossing back to Parapat and arrival at Parapat drive to \r\nSipirok, on the way stop at Pineapple, clove, and coffee plantation and \r\nvisiting traditional market at Balige Sigur-gur and Sipoholon Hot \r\nSprings. Before arrival at Sipirok the day enjoy the nature by walking \r\nat the bank of Sarulla river, the rice terrace and arrival at Sipirok \r\ncheck in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 08 : SIPIROK â€“ BARUMUN NAGARI WILDLIFE SANCTUARY ( Simple guest / Ranger house) B</b><br>Barumun\r\n Nagari is a hidden paradise in Padang Lawas, North Sumatra, a landscape\r\n consisted of rainforest, savanna a perfect place for an elephant \r\nsanctuary. <br>Located in Northern Sumatra, Barumun Nagari Wildlife \r\nSanctuary (BNWS) was established in April 2015 to create a sanctuary for\r\n mistreated elephants from throughout Indonesia. At the sanctuary, there\r\n are currently six elephants being rehabilitated. Here, their \r\nnutritional needs and health concerns are addressed as well as their \r\nmental health. As a result of spending so much time on chains, and being\r\n denied any semblance of a natural life, the elephants developed post \r\ntraumatic stress disorder (PTSD). Now these elephants have 32 ha. of \r\njungle to roam, and sleep in chain free shelters. The aim of the \r\nsanctuary is to provide a place of rest where the elephants can live \r\nwith a sense of peace and dignity. This is the first program of its kind\r\n in the country and will hopefully serve as inspiration for others to \r\ngive these magnificent animals the respect that they deserve.<br>Not \r\nonly elephant but this Sanctuary also inhabited by Sumatra tiger, tapir,\r\n deer, black gibbon, birds and other kind of animal. This sanctuary give\r\n the animal peace and dignity.<br><br>After breakfast at hotel drive to \r\nAek Godang village, it will take about 1 hour driving, from this village\r\n you will drive via palm oil plantation to reach Barumun Nagari Wildlife\r\n Sanctuary (BNWS), arrival at BNWS take a fresh welcome drink and then \r\nwatching a movie about the project of BNWS, and then by jeep Safari at \r\nthe Sanctuary area, you will take to the Savana to see Sumatra elephant \r\ntake care by their mahout, you may join with the mahout during walking \r\nwith the elephant and feed the elephant, then drive to the area where \r\nthe possibility to see the habitat of black gibbon and the sanctuary of \r\nSumatra tiger, during the trip you will also visit to a small lake \r\ncalled Lake Tao, depend on if you are lucky or not, there is a \r\npossibility to see several kind of birds such as Rhino Hornbill and \r\nother kind of birds and other kind of animal such as tapir and deer, \r\nafternoon check in to simple ranger house. <br>Your breakfast, lunch and dinner will provide by the staff of the sanctuary.<br><br><b>DAY 09: BARUMUN NAGARI WILDLIFE SANCTUARYâ€“ BUKITTINGGI ( Royal Denai Hotel / Similar Hotel)Â Â Â  (B)</b><br>Leave\r\n BNWS for Bukittinggi by passing rain tropical forest of Rimba Panti and\r\n stop will be made to see the attraction of monkey picking up the \r\ncoconut. Visit pepper, vanilla, cardamon and cinnamon garden, and \r\ncrossing the equator line at Bonjol, afternoon arrival at Bukittinggi \r\nthe charming towns of Minangkabau directly check in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 10: BUKITTINGGI â€“ MINANGKABAU TOURÂ  (B)</b><br>After\r\n breakfast drive to Batusangkar via Tabek Patah, on the way stop at \r\nRao-Rao to visit Minangkabau traditional village and stop to see \r\ntraditional coffee milling, arrival at Batusangkar drive to Pagaruyung \r\nto visit the Palace of Minangkabau Kingdom, afternoon return to \r\nBukittinggi via Padang Panjang and visit Pandai Sikat village to see \r\nMinangkabau traditional hand weaving and wood carving.<br><br><b>DAY 11:BUKITTINGGI â€“ KERINCI SEBLAT / KERSIK TUO (Subandi Guest House)Â Â  (B)</b><br>After\r\n breakfast drive to Kersik Tuo via Muara labuh and stop at Lake Diatas \r\nand Lake Dibawah and passing several MinangKabau Village. On the way \r\nvisit Telun Berasap Waterfall and passing tea plantation at Kayu Aro and\r\n arrival at Sei Penuh, the area of Kerinci Seblat National Park check in\r\n to hotel and dinner.<br><br><b>DAY 12:Â  LAKE GUNUNG TUJUH TREKKINGÂ  (B,L)</b><br>After\r\n breakfast, transfer by bus to Lake Mount seven National Park for about 1\r\n hours. Lake Danau Tujuh is a huge-mysterious lake on 1.995 m above sea \r\nlevel and surrounded by primary rainforest and 7 hills. Lunch will be \r\nserved on the side of the lake. The pristine area around the lake is \r\nknown as the habitat of Sumatran Tigers, Sumatran Elephants, Primates, \r\nendemic birds of Sumatra as well as research area for the â€œsmall manâ€ \r\nwho live in the jungle around the lake. Most of the day is spent by \r\ntrekking and explore the surrounding in search for animals, birds and \r\nexotic plants. Dinner and overnight at guest house.<br><br><b>DAY 13: KERINCI SEBLAT â€“ ENJOYING THE ATMOSPHERE (B)</b><br>After\r\n breakfast and easy day to enjoy the atmosphere around the area of \r\nKerinci Seblat National park, tour can be made to Kayu Aro Tea \r\nplantation, explore the river around and witness the activities of local\r\n people.<br><br><b>DAY 14: KERINCI SEBLAT â€“ PADANG (The Axana Hotel / Rocky Plaza Hotel)Â Â  (B)</b><br>After\r\n breakfast visiting Semurup Hot Spring, Old Historical Mosque with its \r\nGiant Drum and Lake Kerinci, then drive to Padang via Painan, on the way\r\n stop at Bungus Beach arrival in PadangÂ  check in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 15: HOTEL- AIRPORTÂ  (B)</b><br>After breakfast Free at own leisure until time transfer to Airport. Tour End.<br><br><b>Included:</b><br>-Â Â  Â Accommodation in twin sharing room<br>-Â Â  Â Air condition private car<br>-Â Â  Â Daily breakfast<br>-Â Â  Â Tours<br>-Â Â  Â Transfer<br>-Â Â  Â Entrance fee<br>-Â Â  Â English speaking tour guide<br>-Â Â  Â Jungle tracking at Bukit Lawang 03 hours, included local guide and permit<br>-Â Â \r\n Â Fullday excursion & Safari at Barumun Nagari Sanctuary included \r\nlocal jeepâ€4 wheels driveâ€ elephant feeding, visiting to the area of \r\nblack gibbon, visiting Lake, bird watching and the possibility to see \r\nSumatra tiger sanctuary â€œOnly with certain conditionâ€ due to this area \r\nstill not open for public yet and the possibility to see wild animal \r\ncoming to the area of BNWS in the evening.<br>-Â Â  Â Fullday jungle tracking to Lake Gunung Tujuh at Kerinci Seblat National park.<br>-Â Â  Â Lunch and dinner during stay at Barumun Nagari Sanctuary.<br><br><b>Excluded:</b><br>-Â Â \r\n Â Air fare, airport taxes, insurance, donations, tips, lunch, dinner, \r\ncamera permit at Bukit Lawang and all personal gratuities                                                    </div>                                                                                                        '),
(21, '16 DAYS / 15 NIGHTS EXPLORE LEUSER NATIONAL PARK + LEISURE AT PULAU WEH (North Sumatra & Aceh Province Overland Tour)', 'Discover Sumatra Elephant, Sumatra Orang Utan and other kind of flora and fauna of National park, explore the Jungle of Sumatra and get amazing experience during your holiday in Leuser National park, enjoy the rewarding naturalist\'s experience and exploring the pristine Leuser Ecosystem, Explore the beauty of Weh Island with its white sandy beach and great place for snorkeling & diving. <br>					                                					                                					                                					                                ', '', '<div align=\"justify\">                                                    <b>DAY 01: ARRIVAL IN MEDAN (Emerald Garden Hotel /Le Polonia Hotel / similar) <br></b>Upon arrival at Kualanamu International Airport Medan pick up by our tour guide and then Transfer to hotel, afternoon free at own leisure.<br><br><b>DAY 02: MEDAN â€“ CITY TOUR â€“ TANGKAHANÂ  (Mega Inn Lodge)Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast city tour visiting Sultan Palace, Great Mosque, Chinese Temple and then drive to Tangkahan via Binjai and Batang Serangan. Afternoon arrival at Tangkahan check in at MegaInn Lodge.<br><br><b>DAY 03: TANGKAHAN â€“ ELEPHANT WASHING & RIVER SAFARIÂ Â Â Â Â Â  (B,L)<br></b>After breakfast walking to the elpahant station and then join with the Mahout during washing the elephants, and feed the elephants. After feeding the elephant enjoying Tubing through the river and stop will be made at fantastic Buluh Waterfall where you may enjoy the waterfall, take your natural shower,Â  enjoy sun-bathing and swimming on the river and enjoying picnic lunch by the bank of the river. Afternoon arrival at the village you can get in touch with local people, where you can see the daily activities of the local people and then return to guest house by walking, arrival at guest house you can take a rest or visit hot springs and waterfall near the guest house. <br><br><b>DAY 04: TANGKAHAN â€“ BUKIT LAWANG BY JEEP (Bukit Lawang Cottage / Rindu Alam Hotel / similar)Â Â Â  (B) <br></b>After breakfast leave Tangkahan for Bukit Lawang by Jeep passing plantation and jungle road, on the way stop at plantation and several interesting places for enjoying the panorama and witness the activities of the local people. Upon arrival at Bukit Lawang check-in to hotel. <br><br><b>DAY 05: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ TRACKINGÂ Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast walking to the jungle to start a jungle tracking to explore the nature of Leuser National Park with their flora and fauna, there will be possibility to see Orang Utan in their own habitat and other kind of animals such as Thomas-leaf monkeys, long tail macaque, gibbon, black gibbon and other kind of flora and fauna of tropical rain forest. This tracking will take about 03 hours, after tracking return to hotel.<br>Afternoon free at own leisure to enjoy the nature of Bukit Lawang where you can also walkingto the village around the hotel<br><br><b>DAY 06: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ BRASTAGI (Sinabung Hills Hotel / Sibayak Intl Hotel / Grand Mutiara Hotel)Â Â Â Â  (B) <br></b>After breakfast drive to Brastagi, on the way stop at Sembahe River, passing Sibolangit, and arrival at Brastagi visiting Lhumbini Park with its duplicate of Shwedagon pagoda, afternoon check-in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 07 : SIBAYAK VOLCANO CLIMBINGÂ Â Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>An early morning drive to the slope of Sibayak volcano and then hike up (~3 hrs to go and back) to the summit of Gunung Sibayak will reward you with sweeping views of the surrounding volcano landscape. The volcano is high in geothermal activity with fuming vents spewing out crystalline sulphur which was mined on a small scale in the past. There is a beautiful heart shaped crater lake where love wordings have been formed by visitors using the volcanic rocks.Â  Arrival at the peak of Sibayak volcano enjoying sun rise on the peak of Sibayak volcano and then time for making pictures of the craterÂ Â  spurting out sulfur smoke and then Descend to the volcano base via other side of the volcano and take a dip in one of the hot spring pools to refresh yourself. Visit the vegetables, fruits and flowers markets and savour one of its most famous produce â€“ Markisa (passion fruits) and then return to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 08: BRASTAGIâ€“KETAMBE (Thousand Hill Guesthouse / Friendship Guesthouse)Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Ketambe, on the way visit Batak Karo traditional village at Lingga and then continue drive by passing Bukit Barisan with stop at several interesting places, arrival at Ketambe check-in to simple guesthouse.<br>-Â Â  Â We drive on a bad road to Aceh. Aceh is governed according to Sharia (Islamic jurisprudence), but you do not notice that much of it. In this part of Aceh live many Christians and so you see next to many churches and mosques also unveiled women. Incidentally, you\'ll find that the sharia in Aceh is not very strict. Unveiled women walking on their own property, and in many places you as a non-Muslim just get alcohol. We stay two nights in a basic hotel.<br><br>-Â Â  Â Ketambe is situated in the Gunung Leuser National Park and Bukit Lawang difference is that here are no plantations. Our bungalows are located at the Alas River. The rain forest here is very pristine and you have a greater chance of spotting orangutans here. <br><br><b>DAY 09 : KETAMBE TRACKINGÂ Â Â Â  (B,L)<br></b>After breakfast drive to the park, the starting point for tracking at Leuser National Park, exploring the wildlife, there is possibility to see wild animals such as wildpig, Orangutans, the Thomas-Leaf Monkeys, the Black Gibbons, Maccaque, exotic lizards, snakes and many birds (notably the Hornbill, if you are lucky). Big trees in the jungle and several tropical plants.<br>The journey will break during lunch time with a picnic lunch provided by local guide and after lunch continue to explore deeper the jungle and the rest of afternoon return to guesthouse.<br><br><b>DAY 10 : KETAMBE â€“ TAKENGON (Bayu Hills Hotel / Bunda Hotel)Â Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>The road leads through the impenetrable interior of Aceh. Constantly we meander through the mountains and we have views of villages, valleys with rice fields and pieces of pristine rainforest. This is no way for wimps! In some parts the road is half washed away by landslides or heavy rainfall and our minivans can sometimes just maneuvering along the sharp cliffs. After a beautiful but heavy and long drive we arrive in Takengon.<br><br><b>DAY 11 : TAKENGON FREE AT OWN LEISUREÂ Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>Here in the highlands around Takengon attend Gayo, an ethnic group with its own language and culture. The lively market is a highlight and you will be struck by the almost overwhelming friendliness of the people. It is clear that hardly any tourists come here and you\'re really an attraction.<br><br>Early birds can take the bus to a viewpoint to see the beautiful sunrise over Lake Tawar and Takengon. After this you walk down through forests and coffee plantations. It is also possible to visit the local One One village. This fishing village has a number of good examples of traditional wooden architecture of Aceh. Here you can enjoy lunch at one of the local restaurants.<br><br><b>DAY 12: TAKENGON â€“ BANDA ACEH (Oasis Hotel / Permata Hati Hotel)Â Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>Through a winding road we leave the highlands and descend to the coast. We arrive in Banda Aceh at the end of the afternoon. Immediately you will notice how new and well looked after everything looks here. After the devastating tsunami of December 26, 2004 is with the help of the international community with might and worked on the restoration of the city. The center of the city with the beautiful Mesjid Raya mosque you should not miss. The atmosphere in the city is very relaxed.<br><br><b>DAY 13: BANDA ACEH â€“ PULAU WEH ( Freddieâ€™s Santai Sumur Tiga / Casanemo Guesthouse)Â Â  (B)<br></b>The city of Banda Aceh is more than five kilometers from the coast. It is hard to imagine that the sea has been able to swallow anything far inland. During the ride to the port you will see many traces of the devastation that caused the tsunami. The passenger terminal where the boat to Pulau Weh leaves is brand new. With a fast boat we cross over in an hour. We stay in a charming accommodation in simple bamboo rooms with sea views. You walk into the small sandy beach.<br><br><b>DAY 14 : PULAU WEH - FREE AT OWN LEISUREÂ Â Â  (B)<br></b>Weh Island is large and mountainous. It has some beautiful beaches and offers excellent snorkeling and diving. Please note that you at least 24 hours before your flight departs should not dive! Ask your tour guide for the possibilities. The capital Sabang, with several notable colonial houses and a lively market, is only a few kilometers away.<br><br><b>DAY 15 : PULAU WEH - FREE AT OWN LEISUREÂ Â Â  (B)<br></b>Weh Island is large and mountainous. It has some beautiful beaches and offers excellent snorkeling and diving. Please note that you at least 24 hours before your flight departs should not dive! Ask your tour guide for the possibilities. The capital Sabang, with several notable colonial houses and a lively market, is only a few kilometers away.<br><br><b>DAY 16 : PULAU WEH â€“ BANDA ACEH â€“ AIRPORTÂ Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast transfer to harbor for ferry to Banda Aceh, arrival at Banda Aceh transfer to airport for your flight to next destination.<br><br></div><b>Price Included:<br></b>-Accommodation based on twin / triple sharing room<br>-Air condition private car<br>-Daily breakfast<br>-Tours<br>-Transfers<br>-Entrance fee<br>-English speaking tour guide from Day-01 until Day-13<br>-Elephant washing + elephant feeding at Tangkahan<br>-Tubing at Tangkahan + picnic lunch<br>-Local jeep for transfer from Tangkahan to Bukit Lawang<br>-Jungle tracking at Bukit Lawang (03 hours) included: local guide and permit<br>-Sibayak volcano climbing with local guide<br>-Fullday jungle tracking at Ketambe included: local guide, permit and picnic lunch<br>-Return fast ferry boat crossing from Banda Aceh to Sabang (Weh Island)<br>-Return transfer from Sabang harbor to hotel in Weh Island<br><br><b>Price Excluded:<br></b>-Airfare, airport taxes, insurance, donations, tips, lunch, dinner, elephant riding at Tangkahan, camera permit at National Park and all personal gratuities.<br><br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                '),
(22, '06 DAYS EXPLORE SIBERUT â€“ MENTAWAI PRIMITIVE TRIBE', '<div align=\"justify\">Mentawai tribe living deep in the forests of Siberut Island who were still practising the ancient traditions and rituals of their indigenous culture. Learn about the Mentawai Tribe and join in everydayâ€™s activities! From hunting to fishing, youâ€™llÂ  learn every little secret about the Mentawai people. Explore and enjoy the natural surroundings, jump in the river for a refresh, try local food and stay at a homestay with the locals. It will be an unforgettable adventure in Sumatra. <br></div>					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                ', '', '<div align=\"justify\"><b>                                                                                                        DAY 01 (Saturday/Thursday) : PADANG â€“ SIBERUT â€“ BATÂ  OBAY / BAT ROROGOTÂ Â Â  (L,D) <br></b>After early breakfast, driver will pick you up at the hotel and then transfer to harbor to catch fast boat to Muara Siberut, fast boat leaving at 07.00, this ferry will stop at Sikabaluan and continue to Siberut, arrive in Siberut around 13.00pm and meet with our guide, prepare and report to authority for trekking, continue by local motorized-canoe in the River, stay in Bat Obay / Bat Rorogot.<br><br><b>DAY 02 (Sunday/Friday) : EXPLORING THE NATIVEâ€™S ACTIVITIES IN BAT OBAI/ ROROGOTÂ Â Â Â Â  (B,L,D) <br></b>Wake up for a bath in the river. After having breakfast exploring the daily activities of Nativeâ€™s Mentawai such as : making loincloth, fishing and making tattoo and other daily activities of Mentawai tribe.<br>Â <br><b>DAY 03 (Monday/Saturday) : BAT OBAI / ROROGOT â€“ BUTUIÂ  (B,L,D) <br></b>After breakfast in the morning, continue your trip to Butui by local motorized canoe, it will take about 3-4 hours, arrival at Butui village stay at traditional house of Mentawai called â€œUMAâ€. <br><br><b>DAY 04 (Tuesday/Sunday0 : EXPLORING THE NATIVEâ€™S ACTIVITIES IN BUTUIÂ Â Â Â Â Â Â  (B,L,D) <br></b>After breakfast in the morning, prepare to explore the Nativeâ€™s Mentawai activities, you will see how the Mentawai making poisoneous arrow for hunting and then go for hunting in the jungleÂ  with Mentawai, after hunting you will see how they make Sago (main food of Mentawai) and search for Sago worm and then you will see how to make traditional medicine. Evening you can enjoy traditional dance of Mentawai and also possible to arrange pig feast (Traditional dance and pig feast are optional).<br><br><b>DAY 05 (Wednesday / Monday) : BUTUI â€“ MUNTEIÂ Â  (B,L,D) <br></b>After breakfast, you still have time to enjoy and see the activities of Mentawai and then leaving to Muntei Village by traditional motorized canoe , on the way on the way stop at KULUKUBUK to visit waterfall in the forest, you can swim at waterfall and then return to river to continue your trip to Muntei village, arrival at Muntei village transfer to traditional house of Mentawai for overnight.<br>Â <br><b>DAY 06 (Thursday / Tuesday) : MUNTEIâ€” MUARA SIBERUT â€“ PADANGÂ  (B,L)<br></b>After breakfast free at own leisure or explore the village, at noon transfer to Muara Siberut, to catch fast ferry to Padang, arrive at early evening in Padang. Transfer to your hotel .<br></div><br><b>INCLUDED:<br></b>-Meals as specified in the Itinerary, All food brought from Padang,Â Â  along the Journey in the island the food is carried by porters and cooked by Guide and helped by his crew.<br>-Return transfer from hotel or Airport to harbor by Car<br>-Transfer Padang â€“ Siberut by Reguler Fast ferry vice-versa<br>-Transfer Siberut â€“ Village through river motorized Canoe vice-versa <br>-Accomodation in the jungle atthe local house (UMA)<br>-Licensed English & Mentawai Speaking Guide <br>-Meals during the trip prepare by guide and cook<br>-Stay in Uma (Mentawai traditional house) with thin matrass and Mosquito Net<br>-Guide and Cook<br>Â <br><b>EXCLUDED: <br></b>-Personal Expenses<br>-The Expenses of Out from the Programe <br>-Accommodation & Meals in Padang<br>-Personal Insurance<br>-Any extra cost appeared caused by delay or cancel of the Fast boat                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                '),
(23, '19 DAYS EXPERIENCE NATURE & BEAUTY OF SUMATRA PLUS CUBADAK ISLAND LEISURE', '<div align=\"justify\">Discover Sumatra Elephant,Sumatra Orang Utan and other kind of flora and fauna of National park<br>Explore the Jungle of Sumatra and get amazing experience during your holiday in Leuser National park.<br>Enjoy the rewarding naturalist\'s experience and exploring the pristine Leuser Ecosystem<br>Discover the incredible and diverse beauty highlights in North and West Sumatera by land journeys.<br>Discover the impressive and pristine rainforest of Sumatra, its history, and culture<br>The Secret of North and West Sumatra combined in your tour.<br>Relaxing on the beach of Cubadak Island,slowing down and soaking up the sunshine, stay in a beautiful rustic resort owned by a welcoming French couple, making it a heavenly island hideaway with delicious food to boot. Spend your days hiking to Cubadakâ€™s interior, snorkelling coral reefs and collapsing on the sand. <br></div>					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                ', '', '<p align=\"justify\"><b>                                                    DAY 01: AIRPORT â€“ HOTEL / CITY TOURÂ  (Emerald Garden Hotel /Le Polonia Hotel / similar) <br></b>Arrival at Kualanamu International Airport Medan meet and transfer to hotel and then city tour by visiting Great Mosque, Sultan Palace, Chinese Temple and market , afternoon return back to hotel.<br>Â Â  Â <br><b>DAY 02: MEDAN â€“ TANGKAHAN (Mega Inn Lodge)Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Tangkahan via Binjai and Tanjung Pura, on the way visit several villages where you can see the daily activities of local people, arrival at Tangkahan (a part of Leuser National Park) check in to simple Guesthouse. Afternoon free at own leisure or walking around the area of the hotel. On the bank of the river and the will be possibility to see the elephants washing on the river.<br><br><b>DAY 03: TANGKAHAN â€“ ELEPHANT WASHING & RIVER SAFARIÂ Â Â Â Â Â Â  (B,L)<br></b>After breakfast walking to the elephant station and then joinÂ  with the Mahout during washing the elephant, and then feed the elephant. After feeding the elephant enjoying Tubing through the river and stop will be made at fantastic Buluh Waterfall where you may enjoy the waterfall, take your natural shower and then you can enjoy sun-bathing and swimming on the river and enjoying picnic lunch on the bank of the river. Afternoon arrival at the village you can get in touch with local people, where you can see the daily activities of the local people and then return to guesthouse by walking, arrival at guesthouse you can take a rest or visit hot springs and waterfall near the guesthouse. <br><br><b>DAY 04: TANGKAHAN â€“ BUKIT LAWANG (Bukit Lawang Cottages / Rindu Alam Hotel / similar)Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Bukit Lawang by Jeep , on the way stop at several plantations for rubber, and palm oil, arrival at Bukit Lawang check-in to hotel and afternoon free at own leisure.<br>Â Â  Â Â Â Â  Â Â Â  Â <br><b>DAY 05: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ TRACKINGÂ Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast walking to the jungle to start a jungle tracking to explore the nature of Leuser National Park with its flora and fauna, there will be possibility to see Orang Utan on their own habitat and other kind of animals such as Thomas-leaf monkeys, long tail maccaque, gibbon, black gibbon and other kind of flora and fauna of tropical rain-forest. This tracking will take about 03 hours, after tracking return to hotel.<br>Afternoon free at own leisure to enjoy the nature of Bukit Lawang where you can also walking to the village around the hotel <br><br><b>DAY 06: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ BRASTAGI (Hotel Sinabung Hills / Sibayak Intl Hotel / Grand Mutiara Hotel)Â Â Â Â Â  (B) <br></b>After breakfast drive to Brastagi , on the way stop at Sembahe River, passing Sibolangit, and arrival at Brastagi visiting Lhumbini Park with its duplicate of Shwedagon pagoda, then visit fruit market, and Gundaling Hill. Afternoon check-in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 07: BRASTAGI â€“ SAMOSIR / LAKE TOBA ( Tabo Cottages / Samosir Villa)Â Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Parapat , on the way visit Batak Karo traditional village at Dokan, stop at Sipiso-piso waterfall, visit at Rumah Bolon (Long House) the old palace of Batak Simalungun Kings and Simarjarunjung to see the view of Lake Toba, upon arrival at Parapat crossing to Samosir Island by ferry boat , arriving on Samosir check-in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 08: MOTOR BIKE TOURÂ Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast you may choose to explore Samosir Island â€œthe Land of Batak Toba peopleâ€ by Motorcycle to the Top of Samosir Hill to see small Lake at the Top of the Hill called Sidahoni Lake, where on the way visiting several Batak Toba villages, to see the activities of local people such us visiting children on the school, visiting the village where the local people make traditional hand weaving and other activities. When you prefer tracking, our tour guide will accompany tracking to the jungle on Samosir Island with the possibility to stop at several villages. Afternoon return to hotel. <br><br><b>DAY 09: SAMOSIR FREE AT OWN LEISUREÂ Â  (B)<br></b>Today is a free time to relax, swimming, sun-bathing or walking around the villages and still possible to take a Boat tripÂ  (Optional Tour)<br><br><b>DAY 10: SAMOSIR â€“ SIPIROK (Tor Sibohi Hotel)Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast crossing back to Parapat by ferry boat and arrival at Parapat drive to Sipirok, on the way stop at pineapple, clove, and coffee plantation and visiting traditional market at Balige Sigur-gur and Sipoholon Hotsprings. Before arrival at Sipirok the day enjoy the nature by walking at the bank of Sarulla river, the ricefieldsÂ  terraces and arrival at Sipirok check-in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 11: SIPIROK â€“ BUKITTINGGI (Royal Denai Hotel / Similar)Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>Leave Sipirok for Bukittinggi by passing rain tropical forest of Rimba Panti and stop will be made to see the attraction of monkey picking up the coconut. Visit pepper, vanilla, cardamom and cinnamon garden, and crossing the equator line at Bonjol, afternoon arrival at Bukittinggi - the charming town of Minangkabau people - directly check-in to hotel. <br><br><b>Day 12: BUKITTINGGI â€“ CITY TOUR â€“ HARAU VALLEYÂ Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Payakumbuh and visiting Harau Valley with its Echo, ricefield in terraces, traditional villages and then back to Bukittinggi , visiting Sianok Canyon, Fort De Kock, Museum and Market. Afternoon return back to hotel. Evening enjoy traditional Minangkabau Dance and traditional music performance.<br><br><b>DAY 13: BUKITTINGGI MINANGKABAU TOURÂ Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Batusangkar via Tabek Patah, on the way stop at Rao-Rao to visit Minangkabau traditional village and stop to see traditional coffee milling, arrival at Batusangkar proceed to Pagaruyung to visit the duplicate Palace of Minangkabau Kingdom, afternoon return to Bukittinggi via Padang Panjang and visit Pandai Sikat village to see Minangkabau traditional hand weaving and wood carving.<br>Â  Â <br><b>DAY 14: BUKITTINGGI â€“ EXPLORE LOCAL PEOPLE ACTIVITIESÂ  (B)<br></b>After breakfast visit several villages to see how the local people on their daily activities, such as planting the rice on rice-field, and farmer working on their field which helped by water buffalo, and even experience the local people during harvesting time. On this day will provide traditional fried tapioca or fried banana as your snack cooked at the house of local people.<br>Â Â Â  Â <br><b>DAY 15: BUKITTINGGI â€“ PUNCAK LAWANG TRACKING â€“ BUKITTINGGIÂ Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Puncak Lawang, on the way stop at Koto Gadang village to see traditional silverwork and arrival at Puncak Lawang tracking to Maninjau via Lawang jungle , on the way down to Lake Maninjau enjoying coffee break at traditional coffee shop in the jungle, during the tracking there is opportunity to walk at the bank of ricefield and villages. Upon arrival at Maninjau, enjoying the nature of the lake, afternoon return to Bukittinggi.<br><br><b>Day 16: BUKITTINGGI â€“ PADANG â€“ CUBADAK ISLAND (Cubadak Paradiso Resort)Â Â Â Â Â  (B,D)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Padang via Padang Panjang, on the way stop at Anai waterfall, arrival in Padang transfer to Painan takes another 2 hours and boat crossing to Cubadak Island (30 minutes) , arriving at Cubadak Island check-in to hotel<br><br><b>Day 17: CUBADAK PARADISO ISLANDÂ Â  (B,L,D)<br></b>Today is the activities on the island which will be arranged by the resort, the activities can be covered :<br>-Â Â  Â Snorkelling with its Snorkeling equipment<br>-Â Â  Â Picnic days to neighbouring island (Depend on the weather)<br>-Â Â  Â Canoeing and Fun Sailing<br>-Â Â  Â Tracking in the forest.<br>Fullboard meals (Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner) during stay in the Island included + Free flow of Sumatra tea and Coffee<br><br><b>Day 18: CUBADAK PARADISO ISLANDÂ Â Â Â  (B,L,D)<br></b>Today is the activities on the island which will be arranged by the resort, the activities can be covered :<br>-Â Â  Â Snorkelling with its Snorkeling equipment<br>-Â Â  Â Picnic days to neighbouring island (Depend on the weather)<br>-Â Â  Â Canoeing and Fun Sailing<br>-Â Â  Â Tracking in the forest<br>Fullboard meals (Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner) during stay in the Island included + Free flow of Sumatra tea and Coffee.<br><br><b>Day 19: CUBADAK ISLAND â€“ PADANG / AIRPORTÂ Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast crossing back to Painan by boat and then drive to Padang Airport for your flight to next destination.<br>Tour End<br><br><b>Included : <br></b>- Accommodation based on Twin sharing <br>- Air-Condition private car <br>- Daily Breakfast <br>- Tours <br>- Transfers <br>- Entrance fee <br>- Elephant wshing at Tangkahan + elephant feeding <br>- Tubing at Tangkahan + picnic lunch <br>- local non-ac jeep for transfer from Tangkahan to Bukit Lawang <br>- Jungle tracking at Bukit Lawang (03 hours) included local guide & permit <br>- Excursion at Samosir Island by car Â <br>- Ferry boat crossing Parapat to Samosir and Painan to Cubadak Island vice-versa <br>- Puncak Lawang â€“ Maninjau tracking <br>- English speaking Tour guide (From day 01 until drop off at Padang for Cubadak Island) <br>- Fullboard meals during stay at Cubadak Island, excursion at Cubadak Island (Except diving).<br></p><p><b>Â Excluded :</b> Airfares and airport taxes, Lunch, Dinner, Insurance, Donation, Tips, Elephant riding at Tangkahan, Camera permit at Bukit Lawang and all personal gratuities.<br></p>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        ');
